explanation: The loop 'for i in range(k):' can raise an IndexError if k is greater than n (there are fewer input strings than k). I changed the loop to iterate up to min(k, n) so it never tries to access s[i] out of range.
fixed_code:
n, k = map(int, input().split())
s = [input() for _ in range(n)]
s.sort()
for i in range(min(k, n)):
  print(s[i])
